If you would like to ask an additional question / answer be posted simple email the details to <a href="mailto:webmaster@myLive-Tech.com">webmaster@myLive-Tech.com</a> an a Live-Tech agent will post so upon approval.

[accordion]

[acc_item title="What mobile phones are supported?"]Currently, all iPhones, Android OS, Windows Mobile 5+ OS, Windows Phone all versions, Nokia Mail for Exchange, Palm Pre, and Palm 700p are fully supported.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What are the access methods available?"]We support full MAPI and OWA. We do not sell OWA only.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is the storage limitation for Archiving?"]There are no storage limits for archiving services.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How long is email retained?"]Archiving email is stored up to 10 years[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you offer Legal Hold?"]Yes[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Can I export my mail?"]Yes, you can export in a number of common formats like CSV, pst, txt file etc.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How quickly are messages visible in the archives?"]Archived messages will generally appear within a few hours of being sent of received.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is the attachments limit for incoming and outgoing emails?"]50 MB[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What version of BlackBerry Enterprise Server are you currently running?"]Version 5.X[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you support BlackBerry OS 6?"]We support all versions including the latest 6.0.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you support BlackBerry Public Calendars"]Yes, at an additional cost.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What are my minimum software requirements?"]Windows XP SP2, Outlook 2007 or higher with Safari 4+ or Mozilla 3.6+ or Internet Explorer 7+, Mac OS X with Entourage 2008 EWS or higher with a Safari 4+ or Mozilla 3.6+[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What are my minimum hardware requirements?"]High Speed Internet connection. If you use Outlook Web Access, you will only need a computer that is sufficiently powerful to access the Internet via a Safari 4+ or Mozilla 3.6+ or Internet Explorer 7+[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What protocol or connection type do you use to access your mailbox?"]We use RPC over HTTPS connection[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is the maximum amount of individuals I can add to a Distribution list?"]Unlimited[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How many distribution lists may I create?"]Unlimited[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you permit using email aliases and how many may each user have?"]Yes, they are unlimited.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is your backup policy?"]We do a full backup of all mail stores daily for a maximum period of seven days. Users requiring longer email retention would be recommended to purchase the archive add-on.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is maximum allowable size of my email box?"]According to Microsoft the maximum allowable size is 2TB. We recommend however that you limit your size of mailbox on a local computer to no more than 50GB for performance reasons in regards to indexing file resources and search functionality.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How many emails can be sent and received during a 24 hour period?"]Currently our system allows 1000 outgoing emails to be sent from a single user per day. There is no limit to incoming emails.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you allow catchalls?"]No, we allow unlimited aliases however.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="When are users notified when they are reaching their mailbox quota? "]At 92% users are warned that their mailbox is nearing its capacity. At 100% users are no longer able to send.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What happens if they exceed the threshold?"]At 112% users can no longer send or receive. Plan Upgrade Options Available.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="May I forward emails from my mailbox to another address?"]Yes[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="One of the users wants another user to receive the same email they receive â€“ does this apply?"]For most parts itâ€™s a distribution list ie one email that is sent to multiple people.Â  Otherwise, it would be an email forward if for example if someone sends an email to david@yourdomain.com and you want john@youdomain.com to receive a copy of it.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="One of the users wants another user to receive the same email they receive â€“ does this apply?"]For most parts itâ€™s a distribution list ie one email that is sent to multiple people.Â  Otherwise, it would be an email forward if for example if someone sends an email to <em>david@yourdomain.com</em> and you want <em>john@youdomain.com</em> to receive a copy of it.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Are you a Tier 4 data center?"]Yes[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What connection speeds do you offer to your data center?"]We have two OC48 (one redundant) with a burstable load of 1Gbit/s in our <a title="Our Data Center" href="http://www.livetechexchange.com/our-data-center/" target="_blank">data center</a>[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Can external users migrate to Live-Tech using our Migration Tool?"]Yes, as long as they use a webmail client and have ONE user that can be given full mailbox permission to the mailboxes of all users in their organization.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How long does it take to manually migrate the data of a userâ€™s mailbox?"]Generally itâ€™s about bandwidth and network conditions. The average is 3Gb an hour. Use this as a benchmark when asking how large each userâ€™s mailbox is.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What version of Outlook may I use?"]Outlook 2007, Outlook 2010 or Outlook 2011 for Mac. Outlook 2003 is no longer supported.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Is there any additional cost for software or If I donâ€™t have Outlook?"]No. Each <a title="About Live-Tech Exchange" href="http://www.livetechexchange.com/about-exchange-2010/" target="_blank">mailbox</a> includes Free Software Licensing for Outlook &amp; Entourage (PC &amp; Mac).[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How often do passwords expire?"]Our Control Panel allows you to control the length, complexity as well as the duration of password expiry.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="How much storage does one receive?"]We offer 100MB per user up to a maximum of 2GB. If you need more space, we recommend that you consider at using SharePoint Foundations 2010.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Who do you use for virus/spam filtering?"]Cloudmark - <em>www.cloudmark.com</em> [/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Do you allow Blacklists and whitelists?"]Yes [/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Can users modify their whitelists and blacklists or is this strictly controlled via an Admin."]Yes. We also offer Admin level of control to prevent or allow users to modify their whitelists and blacklists respectively.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="Can customers buy their own SSL Certs?"]No. SSL Certs are installed and maintained by the Hosting team. We are unable to support unless we own the certificate.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="What is the URL for OWA?"]<a title="Outlook WebApp" href="http://www.LiveTechExchange.com/owa" target="_blank">http://www.LiveTechExchange.com/owa</a>[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="I thought Exchange services were pricey and made just for enterprise."] No... thanks to the evolution of technology <a title="About Live-Tech Exchange" href="http://www.livetechexchange.com/about-exchange-2010/" target="_blank">Live-Tech Hosted Exchange</a> handles everything for you so you do not need extensive hardware or techs around the clock at you to ensure up-time. All this is done and managed for you by us. You can get just 1 account or 100's based on your size and needs.[/acc_item]

[acc_item title="I ran out of space, now what do I do"]Live-Tech makes upgrades easy and painless. Just simplyÂ <a title="Contact Us" href="http://www.livetechexchange.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">send us a request</a> and your plan will be altered accordingly. [/acc_item]

[acc_item title="My Question is not listed here. How I can ASK ?"] If you have any questions then, please feel free toÂ <strong><a title="Contact Us" href="http://www.livetechexchange.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">Contact Us</a></strong>Â online. Our team will contact you back soon.Â [/acc_item]

